==Latin==

===Etymology===
In post-classical Latin (4th or 5th century) in reference to a sum of money due each year.
Already in the 3rd century in the sense of "through the year". From the preposition {{term|per||lang=la|during}} + {{term|annum||lang=la}}, the accusative singular of {{term|annus||lang=la|year}}.

===Adverb===
